headline: Sysco (SYY) Margin Dip Reinforces Financial Position Risks as Earnings Growth Slows
summary: Sysco (SYY) is forecasting earnings growth of 10.01% per year, with annual revenue projected to rise by 4.1%. Net profit margins currently stand at 2.2%, down from 2.4% last year. Average annual earnings growth over the past five years reached 33% as Sysco returned to profitability. With growth expected to trail the broader US market, investors are focused on how valuation discounts and a reliable dividend balance against recent margin pressure. See our full analysis for Sysco.
